=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">yeah I guess whatever</a=
>=E2=80=9D:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">From Manhattan=E2=80=99s Oculus<a class=3D"foo=
tnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-6" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !importa=
nt; display: inline-block;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a> building to a=C2=A0co-working space in Southern California, Americans =
are getting their irises scanned by a chrome=C2=A0orb=C2=A0that=C2=A0Sam Al=
tman=C2=A0helped create.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Unlike the roughly 2 million people around the=
=C2=A0world who=E2=80=99ve completed similar scans in exchange for payment,=
 these US registrants=C2=A0aren=E2=80=99t getting much of value from=C2=A0W=
orldcoin, the=C2=A0OpenAI=C2=A0chief executive's latest crypto project.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Drawn by a promotional blitz for an undertakin=
g that has raised=C2=A0privacy=C2=A0and=C2=A0ethics=C2=A0concerns, a few or=
b pilgrims in New York, Los Angeles and Miami hoped they'd get some crypto =
for their troubles, while others were drawn by Altman himself.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Alex Chung, a user in Los Angeles, planned to =
make a YouTube video about his experience.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIf I scan my eyes, I can get 25 coins=
,=E2=80=9D he said. When he learned that wasn=E2=80=99t true, he said he ho=
ped to get the tokens =E2=80=9Csome day in the future.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Worldcoin's token launched on Monday at $1.70 =
and jumped as high as $3.58 before falling to around $2.18 on Friday, data =
compiled by CoinMarketCap showed. =E2=80=A6 Outside the US, Worldcoin hands=
 out a few of its=C2=A0own crypto tokens, in increments worth about $50, to=
 entice people to share their biometric data.=C2=A0In the US, where Altman =
has said the crypto regulatory landscape is uncertain, the reasons for sign=
ing up are still mostly hypothetical.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CSam Altman is interesting =E2=80=94 h=
e=E2=80=99s not only motivated by money,=E2=80=9D said Alberto Simon, who c=
ame through a downtown Manhattan store called the Canvas for a scan on Tues=
day. =E2=80=9CI like random tech stuff.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI don=E2=80=99t think I have any actu=
al use for this right now,=E2=80=9D said Ben Deeb, who stopped by to offer =
up his irises in Los Angeles. =E2=80=9CI just like trying out things. Plus,=
 I=E2=80=99m a TV writer on strike. I figured I got the time.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Nobody is going to turn down getting their eye=
s scanned by a chrome orb, that is just science. Oh a guy is building a sup=
erintelligent AI and also compiling a permanent electronic identification d=
atabase of all humans, that=E2=80=99s great, that=E2=80=99s not an alarming=
 science-fiction premise at all. I feel like if you made that movie you=E2=
=80=99d have to have some plausible back story about how the AI convinced p=
eople to hand over their iris scans to the AI, but in the real world you do=
n=E2=80=99t.</p>
